WEBVTT

00:08.250 --> 00:10.208
Previously on Billions...

00:12.375 --> 00:13.291
Lara?

00:13.291 --> 00:15.291
Boys?

00:15.291 --> 00:17.000
Ice Juice.
I can take it over.

00:17.000 --> 00:17.959
Just need the cash.

00:17.959 --> 00:19.333
You know my money's
in a blind trust.

00:19.333 --> 00:23.041
Congratulations. All the
analysts now answer to you.

00:23.041 --> 00:24.834
If I fill in those blanks,
I have to put my name on it.

00:24.834 --> 00:26.834
We've long suspected

00:26.834 --> 00:28.500
criminal activity
at Axe Capital.

00:28.500 --> 00:30.583
You have nothing on Axe Cap
and even less on me.

00:30.583 --> 00:31.583
Hey, hey.

00:31.583 --> 00:33.625
I tried calling.

00:33.625 --> 00:34.917
Phone's been off.

00:34.917 --> 00:36.583
I'm going to go put
the boys to bed.

00:37.667 --> 00:41.041
I am so close
to getting Axe.

00:41.041 --> 00:44.542
You will get him...
on something else.

00:44.542 --> 00:46.583
Sandicot is a circle.

00:46.583 --> 00:48.375
It leads right back to you.

00:48.375 --> 00:52.875
I  think I'll get Axe
on something else.

00:52.875 --> 00:53.333
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:00.583 --> 01:04.041
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:13.834 --> 01:17.625
♪ Tom Petty's
"Even the Losers"  ♪

01:17.625 --> 01:20.041
Everybody pays.

01:20.041 --> 01:23.083
♪ Well,
it was nearly summer...  ♪

01:23.083 --> 01:24.834
Yes, yes, yes.

01:24.834 --> 01:26.750
I understand, Terry.

01:26.750 --> 01:29.750
And that's why
if I get paid on time next week,

01:29.750 --> 01:33.375
which, when you're a contractor,
you never really know.

01:33.375 --> 01:38.000
But then, of course I pay you,
Terry, right away,

01:38.000 --> 01:40.250
first fucking thing
I do.

01:40.250 --> 01:42.333
That's a relief.

01:42.333 --> 01:44.542
Isn't it, Johnny?

01:44.542 --> 01:45.834
A sweet relief.

01:45.834 --> 01:49.583
Some guys, no matter how
well-intentioned they may be,

01:49.583 --> 01:53.583
hmm, they can't see to find
the money when it's owed...

01:53.583 --> 01:57.834
which leads to uncomfortable
conversations like this one.

01:57.834 --> 02:00.375
Terry,
I'm well-intended.

02:00.375 --> 02:02.417
You're a good guy,
Slayton.

02:02.417 --> 02:04.667
And I-I'll
tell you something.

02:04.667 --> 02:08.959
I never considered myself
a bad guy, hmm?

02:08.959 --> 02:10.917
Do you think
I'm a bad guy?

02:10.917 --> 02:11.625
No.
Good.

02:11.625 --> 02:13.750
Ohh!

02:18.834 --> 02:20.125
Wives.

02:20.125 --> 02:22.959
They got
all the leverage.

02:22.959 --> 02:25.333
So I had to do something
to even the score.

02:25.333 --> 02:29.834
See, now you have
a compelling reason to pay me

02:29.834 --> 02:32.083
when she wants
to pay the credit cards.

02:32.083 --> 02:33.291
Yes.

02:33.291 --> 02:34.625
I do.

02:34.625 --> 02:37.542
I owe you, Terry.

02:37.542 --> 02:40.125
And I'm gonna
make things right...

02:40.125 --> 02:43.083
no matter
what I have to do.

02:43.083 --> 02:47.917
♪ Baby, even the losers  ♪

02:47.917 --> 02:49.667
♪ Get lucky sometimes...  ♪

02:49.667 --> 02:52.667
Was a time folks in your job
had the sense

02:52.667 --> 02:56.500
to duck my fucking call
until you had good news for me.

02:57.792 --> 03:02.667
♪ Get lucky sometimes,
oh, oh, oh, oh  ♪

03:06.625 --> 03:07.750
Remind me
the next time I forget,

03:07.750 --> 03:11.125
there is no one in this business
who won't sell you out

03:11.125 --> 03:13.333
if they think there's
a fucking nickel in it.

03:13.333 --> 03:15.834
I find that
strangely reassuring.

03:15.834 --> 03:18.166
Eliminates the possibility
of disillusionment.

03:18.166 --> 03:20.500
Yes. Yes.
Let the idealists

03:20.500 --> 03:22.417
and romantics
get their hearts broken

03:22.417 --> 03:24.166
while the hard-bitten
pragmatists--

03:24.166 --> 03:25.375
Wow.

03:25.375 --> 03:28.500
You have something you really
don't want to tell me about.

03:28.500 --> 03:29.458
What happened?

03:29.458 --> 03:31.542
They shoot Sonny
on the causeway?

03:31.542 --> 03:33.959
Otherwise,
spit it the fuck out.

03:33.959 --> 03:34.792
Boyd was right.

03:34.792 --> 03:36.250
I just hung up
with Patriot Bank.

03:36.250 --> 03:39.208
After a wet
and hot road show,

03:39.208 --> 03:42.041
they are taking out
the Ice Juice IPO.

03:42.041 --> 03:44.875
Press is getting loaded up
with the story as we speak.

03:44.875 --> 03:45.542
Shit.

03:45.542 --> 03:47.792
They think
it's a winner?

03:47.792 --> 03:49.708
They do.
There's more.

03:49.708 --> 03:51.208
Charles Rhoades Sr.
did take

03:51.208 --> 03:52.542
an Uncle Miltie-sized position
in the company.

03:52.542 --> 03:56.125
I've run through it
with the primes all over town,

03:56.125 --> 03:58.166
theirs, ours,
the other guy's,

03:58.166 --> 04:00.000
and with analysts
at the big three,

04:00.000 --> 04:01.291
as well
as our own people.

04:01.291 --> 04:03.041
They all agree
with Patriot.

04:03.041 --> 04:04.041
- Fundamentals?
- Solid.

04:04.041 --> 04:06.625
The projections
are real.

04:06.625 --> 04:08.750
They're rolling out
the IPO soon.

04:08.750 --> 04:10.625
Everyone thinks
it's gonna work.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.875
No one sees a short play
we can make.

04:12.875 --> 04:14.750
I don't see
an avenue of attack.

04:14.750 --> 04:16.875
Personnel?
The fucking lawyer,

04:16.875 --> 04:19.792
Ira Schirmer, represented
Rhoades at your deposition.

04:19.792 --> 04:20.750
He's got a board seat.

04:20.750 --> 04:23.625
Rhoades' father
and his closest confidante

04:23.625 --> 04:27.417
have both jumped headfirst
into a business...together?

04:27.417 --> 04:28.250
And you amble in here
to tell me

04:28.250 --> 04:30.667
that I have no way
to wreck it?

04:30.667 --> 04:31.875
Fuck.

04:31.875 --> 04:33.458
This is  Sonny
on the causeway.

04:43.583 --> 04:45.708
Top sheet
says Charles Rhoades Sr.

04:45.708 --> 04:47.583
is a high-net-worth
individual. He has

04:47.583 --> 04:50.208
multiple business holdings,
mostly in real estate.

04:50.208 --> 04:52.583
But at the moment,
it seems he's largely illiquid

04:52.583 --> 04:54.417
because of some new
cash-intensive

04:54.417 --> 04:55.041
real-estate investments.

04:55.041 --> 04:56.417
Fucker's house-poor?

04:56.417 --> 04:59.792
Houses.
City co-op, Hamptons place,

04:59.792 --> 05:01.458
a hobby farm
in Mount Kisco,

05:01.458 --> 05:03.250
an ocean-front spread
in Florida.

05:03.250 --> 05:05.417
And upstate, he bought up
half of Kingsford.

05:05.417 --> 05:07.291
But he won't be able to flip
that land for a real profit

05:07.291 --> 05:10.834
until the casino
is in and open.

05:10.834 --> 05:12.875
And so
the question is...

05:12.875 --> 05:15.583
Yes. Where did he get the
capital for the juice company?

05:15.583 --> 05:17.375
I did a forensic look,
and I cannot find the source.

05:17.375 --> 05:19.583
Which means there's no
institutional money

05:19.583 --> 05:22.792
behind the purchase
of his share of Ice Juice.

05:22.792 --> 05:24.458
It had to be a personal loan
of some sort.

05:26.458 --> 05:26.959
Okay. Good.

05:26.959 --> 05:29.834
Thank you, Taylor.

05:33.917 --> 05:36.333
So, Rhoades Sr.
got his money for Ice Juice

05:36.333 --> 05:38.500
from a personal loan.

05:38.500 --> 05:41.959
Had to be someone
very close to him

05:41.959 --> 05:43.166
to lend him
that kind of jack.

05:43.166 --> 05:47.458
Maybe a little too  close.

05:47.458 --> 05:49.625
♪ dramatic music  ♪

05:49.625 --> 05:53.875
You know those poison-tip arrows
that certain tribes use

05:53.875 --> 05:56.208
that go through one guy
and kill another?

05:56.208 --> 05:59.166
This might be
like that.

05:59.166 --> 05:59.875
Yeah.

