outlets calling for comment,

34:05.375 --> 34:08.542
social media, the press.
People are getting sick.

34:08.542 --> 34:10.208
Something's breaking out.

34:10.208 --> 34:12.375
They don't know
if it's listeria

34:12.375 --> 34:14.041
or Legionnaires'
or what the fuck it is.

34:14.041 --> 34:16.041
- You have a TV, put it on.
- I'm not gonna

34:16.041 --> 34:18.166
turn on my TV, Ira.
Tell me what I'd see.

34:18.166 --> 34:20.041
People getting
loaded into ambulances,

34:20.041 --> 34:22.000
reports of illness
going back several weeks,

34:22.000 --> 34:23.750
which my fucking clients
failed to mention.

34:23.750 --> 34:26.250
The stock was getting pummeled
so badly, they halted trading.

34:26.250 --> 34:27.375
The smart money's
fled to safety,

34:27.375 --> 34:30.708
and when that happens,
the bottom drops out.

34:30.708 --> 34:32.500
When trading resumes,
the deal's gonna break.

34:32.500 --> 34:34.542
That's when you go below
the original deal price,

34:34.542 --> 34:35.291
and th-that's...

34:35.291 --> 34:36.041
an unmitigated disaster.

34:36.041 --> 34:37.750
Yeah. This is, uh...

34:37.750 --> 34:41.458
This is fucking horrible.

34:41.458 --> 34:43.083
Is there any way
you can sell?

34:43.083 --> 34:45.375
Chuck, my stock's
all restricted.

34:45.375 --> 34:46.708
Officer class, Ira.

34:46.708 --> 34:48.583
Keep it together.

34:48.583 --> 34:53.333
♪ dramatic music  ♪

34:59.917 --> 35:02.917
Son of a bitch.

35:02.917 --> 35:06.625
Rudy,
I've brought you in last

35:06.625 --> 35:08.917
because when I look at this
on a purely results-based model,

35:08.917 --> 35:11.834
that's where you stand...
last.

35:11.834 --> 35:13.291
Last?

35:13.291 --> 35:14.834
Really?

35:16.583 --> 35:17.792
I'm really last.

35:17.792 --> 35:20.000
By the numbers,
yes, dead last.

35:20.000 --> 35:21.750
My -- My name isn't Rudy.

35:21.750 --> 35:22.417
It's Peter.

35:22.417 --> 35:25.041
Oh.
Do you prefer Peter?

35:25.041 --> 35:26.083
No.

35:26.083 --> 35:29.125
And I love
that they call me Rudy.

35:29.125 --> 35:30.458
You know why?

35:30.458 --> 35:31.750
No.

35:31.750 --> 35:35.542
It's because this place is like
Notre Dame was for him.

35:35.542 --> 35:36.959
The real Rudy.

35:36.959 --> 35:39.166
I was
a high-school fuck-up.

35:39.166 --> 35:42.250
But I impressed a teacher,
got into Hofstra.

35:42.250 --> 35:43.917
I saw Axe speak there,

35:43.917 --> 35:47.083
and from that moment,
this is all I dreamed about.

35:47.083 --> 35:49.125
Being here
at Axe Capital?

35:49.125 --> 35:50.166
Yes. The next time
Axe showed on campus,

35:50.166 --> 35:52.542
I asked him
a smart question,

35:52.542 --> 35:55.291
one that I had thought about,
planned out ahead of time,

35:55.291 --> 35:57.375
and he said to see him
when I got out,

35:57.375 --> 35:58.375
he'd find a place
for me. He did.

35:58.375 --> 36:02.458
But I figured
he'd be like my coach here,

36:02.458 --> 36:06.041
and, well, he hasn't
been that...at all.

36:06.041 --> 36:09.458
Just -- Just been left
to figure it out for myself.

36:11.500 --> 36:14.000
Well, there's no janitor
with a heart of gold

36:14.000 --> 36:16.208
here to root you on,

36:16.208 --> 36:18.583
and no one gets on this field
unless they are the fastest,

36:18.583 --> 36:22.542
strongest, or most talented
person on the depth chart.

36:22.917 --> 36:24.708
I know.

36:24.708 --> 36:28.333
And I know
I don't really belong,

36:28.333 --> 36:31.667
on paper
or in any other way.

36:33.250 --> 36:36.208
But if I somehow make it
out of this room alive,

36:36.208 --> 36:39.542
you won't see another person
in this place work harder,

36:39.542 --> 36:43.000
longer,
faster than me.

36:43.000 --> 36:44.458
I promise.

37:03.291 --> 37:03.834
Yes!

37:06.041 --> 37:09.250
Rudy! Rudy! Rudy!

37:09.250 --> 37:11.708
Rudy! Rudy! Rudy! Rudy! Rudy!

