37:55.250 --> 37:56.583
Donna!

38:00.542 --> 38:02.208
Have the kid
get in here

38:02.208 --> 38:05.250
and get this fucking software
off my computer.

38:05.250 --> 38:09.291
I have
no more use for it.

38:14.792 --> 38:19.291
Well, if old Rhoades Sr.
was counting on any liquidity

38:19.291 --> 38:23.375
from this particular venture,
he is sadly mistaken

38:23.375 --> 38:25.959
'cause this is leaving him
cash-strapped and tits-up.

38:25.959 --> 38:27.250
Speaking of cash,

38:27.250 --> 38:29.500
this could have him
looking to sell Palm Beach.

38:29.500 --> 38:30.667
Ooh, the pride and joy.

38:30.667 --> 38:34.125
If you knew how many times
I'd seen that crusty bastard

38:34.125 --> 38:35.959
strutting around
Mar-a-Lago,

38:35.959 --> 38:38.083
bragging about
his better frontage.

38:38.083 --> 38:39.041
You know what?

38:39.041 --> 38:41.250
Have someone down there
ready to pounce

38:41.250 --> 38:43.083
if the place
hits the market.

38:43.083 --> 38:44.291
Straw bidder.

38:44.291 --> 38:48.125
Yeah, I'll scoop it up cheap
when the clearance sale starts.

38:48.125 --> 38:51.000
Trading on ICEJ resumed just
in time for the closing bell.

38:51.000 --> 38:53.959
Care to watch the docking
of the Hindenburg?

38:53.959 --> 38:56.667
♪ dramatic music  ♪

38:56.667 --> 38:58.125
Ding, ding, ding!

38:58.125 --> 39:00.166
Closing price,

39:00.166 --> 39:04.125
three, eighty-nine.

39:04.125 --> 39:05.875
Stillborn.

39:05.875 --> 39:07.166
Reuters says,

39:07.166 --> 39:09.417
Fresh-Squeezed Chapter 11
in its future."

39:09.417 --> 39:12.208
This is one
busted-ass IPO.

39:12.208 --> 39:14.834
Let's crack open
that bottle.

39:16.208 --> 39:19.000
Just need your signature
on the trading report.

39:20.375 --> 39:21.500
Mm.

39:21.500 --> 39:23.500
We crushed it today.

39:23.500 --> 39:25.875
Oh, oh,
what is this?

39:25.875 --> 39:27.333
What?

39:27.333 --> 39:29.834
The big ICEJ allocation
to the New Beginnings fund.

39:29.834 --> 39:31.750
What the fuck?
Wendy Rhoades wanted in.

39:31.750 --> 39:34.750
She called in the request right
before the thing went south.

39:34.750 --> 39:36.375
She took down a huge
chunk of change for herself.

39:36.375 --> 39:38.166
I assumed
it came from you, Axe.

39:38.166 --> 39:40.291
It fucking didn't.

39:40.291 --> 39:43.875
You notify me next time
she makes a request like that

39:43.875 --> 39:45.500
before  you fucking
fulfill it...

39:45.500 --> 39:48.375
unless you want to start
thinking about

39:48.375 --> 39:50.750
another career
besides trading equities.

39:50.750 --> 39:52.625
You got it.

39:52.625 --> 39:54.583
Fuck. Sorry.

39:54.583 --> 39:55.875
Fuck.

39:56.667 --> 39:59.458
What do you think
she knew?

39:59.458 --> 40:00.875
Not sure.

40:00.875 --> 40:02.291
Either way,
it's a strong move

40:02.291 --> 40:05.041
betting against the family
like that.

40:05.041 --> 40:07.708
Paid off.

40:07.708 --> 40:12.667
♪ dramatic music  ♪

40:47.750 --> 40:50.166
Who'd you can?
Oh.

40:52.083 --> 40:54.875
I didn't do it
to be perceived as tough,

40:54.875 --> 40:56.375
but to make it clear
that if you survive today,

40:56.375 --> 40:59.041
you are now officially
on the team

40:59.041 --> 41:02.083
and wouldn't have to keep
looking over your shoulder.

41:02.083 --> 41:03.542
Yeah, yeah.
Someone still

41:03.542 --> 41:06.291
got a stake through the heart,
and I want to know who.

41:06.291 --> 41:08.041
I could have justified
firing Rudy.

41:08.041 --> 41:09.458
He's still
finding his footing.

41:09.458 --> 41:11.458
But he's scrappy
and deserves the chance.

41:11.458 --> 41:14.083
So I fired
Pununzio instead.

41:14.083 --> 41:15.792
He's kind of a weasel.

41:15.792 --> 41:17.959
Good a reason
as any.

41:17.959 --> 41:20.875
And now
you're baptized by blood.

41:22.458 --> 41:24.041
I need a drink.

41:24.041 --> 41:25.708
Like a real drink?

41:25.708 --> 41:26.750
Yeah.

41:26.750 --> 41:30.125
Maybe like a whole bottle
of a real drink.

41:50.834 --> 41:54.166
You're not gonna be
in that clown car for long.

41:54.166 --> 41:55.208
I love it.
It's a great car.

41:58.583 --> 42:00.959
Look, I didn't want
to do this on site.

42:00.959 --> 42:03.166
That's why I offered
to take you to coffee.

42:03.166 --> 42:05.500
Do what?

42:06.458 --> 42:08.333
This is for you.

42:08.333 --> 42:12.000
Open it up.

42:14.625 --> 42:17.542
That's $250,000 dollars...

42:17.542 --> 42:22.041
as a personal thank-you
from me to you, on Klaxon.

42:22.041 --> 42:24.000
And I'm cheap as fuck.

42:24.000 --> 42:26.792
I'm well-compensated,
more than well-compensated.

42:26.792 --> 42:28.708
Yeah, officially
and on the books,

42:28.708 --> 42:31.208
with records
of the transactions everywhere.

42:32.708 --> 42:35.875
But I wanted to spiff you
above that.

42:35.875 --> 42:39.917
Everyone in our line
needs cash squirreled away.

42:39.917 --> 42:42.750
It can make
all the difference.

42:42.750 --> 42:43.750
Believe me.

42:44.875 --> 42:47.250
I can see
you are telling the truth.

42:47.250 --> 42:48.375
Then believe me
when I say this.

42:48.375 --> 42:51.917
There's more coming...

42:51.917 --> 42:54.166
more of all of it.

42:54.166 --> 42:56.166
♪ dramatic music  ♪

42:56.166 --> 42:59.208
It took me a while...

42:59.208 --> 43:03.208
but now I understand
exactly what Axe sees in you.

43:03.208 --> 43:08.125
♪ dramatic music  ♪

43:08.125 --> 43:10.083
Have a good night.

43:31.083 --> 43:35.458
Did I actually hear Mom
crying from the other room?

43:35.458 --> 43:37.250
Might have been me.

43:37.250 --> 43:40.917
You want to play
the "on paper" game now?

43:40.917 --> 43:43.000
I'm down millions today.

43:43.000 --> 43:45.667
I can't believe
how much goddamn money I lost.

43:45.667 --> 43:49.291
It was never yours
to begin with.

43:49.291 --> 43:51.041
You got to
get it in the boat

43:51.041 --> 43:52.708
before you can hang it
on the goddamn wall.

43:52.708 --> 43:54.875
Only thing to do
in a case like this

43:54.875 --> 43:58.959
is write off the loss
against your cap gains.

43:58.959 --> 44:00.792
This was supposed to be
my cap gain.

44:00.792 --> 44:05.125
Anyway, I-I should be
apologizing to you.

44:05.125 --> 44:07.458
Fucking right.

44:07.458 --> 44:10.291
But you should really
apologize to your friend,

44:10.291 --> 44:13.125
since he's the one who
took the actual pounding.

44:13.125 --> 44:14.917
Dad.

44:16.125 --> 44:19.333
Oh, God.

44:19.333 --> 44:23.750
No, Chuck, you didn't --
you didn't go into your trust?

44:23.750 --> 44:24.625
I authorized it.

44:24.625 --> 44:28.959
I had
that much confidence in it.

44:28.959 --> 44:30.375
And you, Ira.

44:31.417 --> 44:33.333
I'd do it again.

44:33.333 --> 44:36.291
It was
a fluke thing.

44:36.291 --> 44:39.208
The whole eight-
million-dollar equity piece?

44:39.208 --> 44:40.458
Yes.

44:40.458 --> 44:42.083
That's where we started.

44:42.083 --> 44:45.625
What?

44:45.625 --> 44:46.792
- Dad?
- It was rolling.

44:46.792 --> 44:49.291
The thing
was a complete monster.

44:49.291 --> 44:51.834
And what you do...

44:51.834 --> 44:56.291
when you have an advantage
is press it.

44:57.291 --> 44:59.625
How much?

44:59.625 --> 45:02.792
All of it.

45:05.583 --> 45:10.834
So, my entire trust is...

45:10.834 --> 45:12.917
Gone.

45:12.917 --> 45:15.333
I'm gonna throw up.

45:16.583 --> 45:21.333
Well, you did have
that Ice Juice today.

45:25.875 --> 45:28.792
♪ dramatic music  ♪

45:44.834 --> 45:49.208
I've never used
the word swanky  before,

45:49.208 --> 45:51.750
but that's what
this building is swanky.

45:51.750 --> 45:53.792
I wouldn't use
that word, either,

45:53.792 --> 45:55.375
but I can't say
you're wrong.

45:55.375 --> 45:56.792
It must feel good.

45:56.792 --> 46:00.750
My own apartment's probably
a quarter the size of yours,

46:00.750 --> 46:05.041
in a part of town that's
considerably worse than this.

46:05.041 --> 46:05.959
During the winter,

46:05.959 --> 46:08.125
the heat pipes bang
practically all night.

46:08.125 --> 46:09.166
I grew up
in a place like that.

46:09.166 --> 46:11.375
Mm.

46:11.375 --> 46:14.792
Sometimes I look
at my surroundings

46:14.792 --> 46:17.875
and wonder
why I stay...

46:17.875 --> 46:18.750
doing what I do.

46:18.750 --> 46:21.166
I mean,
your boss offered

46:21.166 --> 46:22.917
to put me
in a place like this.

46:22.917 --> 46:23.917
Really?
Oh, yeah.

46:23.917 --> 46:25.750
Practically got
on his hands and knees

46:25.750 --> 46:27.333
and begged me
to work for him.

46:27.333 --> 46:28.917
And the night
I turned him down,

46:28.917 --> 46:32.208
when I got home
and looked around my place,

46:32.208 --> 46:35.458
for about ten minutes,
I felt like an idiot.

46:35.458 --> 46:37.125
I can understand that.

46:37.125 --> 46:40.917
Then I fell straight asleep
'cause I had a clean conscience.

46:40.917 --> 46:43.208
I was where
I was supposed to be,

46:43.208 --> 46:44.458
doing the right thing.

46:44.458 --> 46:45.834
I am happy
for you.

46:45.834 --> 46:49.417
And now
I'm going to go inside.

46:49.417 --> 46:50.834
Yeah.
You can in a second.

46:50.834 --> 46:53.500
But as you're putting your head
on your pillow tonight,

46:53.500 --> 46:56.125
I want you to think about
what you're really trading on

46:56.125 --> 46:58.875
in order to live here,
work there, be who you are.

46:58.875 --> 47:01.625
I think about it
all the time.

47:01.625 --> 47:03.708
That means
there's still hope...

47:03.708 --> 47:06.250
because soon, you'll never
think about it again.

47:06.250 --> 47:10.750
You will just glide along, rich,
with even bigger apartments

47:10.750 --> 47:13.500
and nicer watches
and faster planes,

47:13.500 --> 47:18.291
only none of it will matter
to you at all.

47:18.291 --> 47:20.458
We never use the words
we really mean.

47:20.458 --> 47:21.500
Like "swanky"?
No.

47:21.500 --> 47:23.333
Like "soul."

47:23.333 --> 47:25.000
Your soul.

47:25.000 --> 47:28.291
Axelrod will demand things
of you incrementally

47:28.291 --> 47:32.542
that will change the fundamental
nature of who you are,

47:32.542 --> 47:35.834
and I am here because
I can give it back to you.

47:35.834 --> 47:39.333
I don't believe
in the soul...

47:39.333 --> 47:41.625
not in the way
it's traditionally used,

47:41.625 --> 47:43.125
nor in
the more modern meaning,

47:43.125 --> 47:45.959
which connotes connectedness
and being spiritually awake.

47:45.959 --> 47:49.583
What I do  believe in
are actions, purpose,

47:49.583 --> 47:51.291
purity of vocation,

47:51.291 --> 47:54.166
and the challenges that
come along with those things,

47:54.166 --> 47:56.375
the things that
make me feel alive.

47:56.375 --> 47:58.125
Axe Capital gives me
all of that and more.

48:00.667 --> 48:03.208
So, you worry
about my soul,

48:03.208 --> 48:06.083
and I'll just
keep doing my job.

48:22.417 --> 48:26.834
I figured on a little more wow
factor for two-thousand bucks.

48:26.834 --> 48:28.667
I had the rest dropped off
at the hospital.

48:28.667 --> 48:32.083
Very thoughtful
of you.

48:35.166 --> 48:38.333
You know
who you look like right now?

48:38.333 --> 48:40.125
Who?

48:41.708 --> 48:45.542
Bobby fucking Axelrod.

48:45.542 --> 48:48.250
It's been a while.

48:48.250 --> 48:50.417
Well,
I had a good day.

48:50.417 --> 48:52.083
I'm glad you noticed.

48:52.083 --> 48:53.500
Oh, I notice.

48:53.500 --> 48:57.750
I'm not the one who takes
shit between us for granted.

48:57.750 --> 48:58.875
You're right.

48:58.875 --> 49:01.583
And that's why I was trying
to formalize my apology

49:01.583 --> 49:04.291
with the flowers.

49:06.166 --> 49:07.875
Then I formally accept.

49:07.875 --> 49:13.291
So, we can
start over from here?

49:15.291 --> 49:18.375
Yeah.

49:23.834 --> 49:26.792
So, this is like
a first date?

49:26.792 --> 49:29.708
Sure.

49:34.125 --> 49:36.166
Tell me something
about yourself.

49:36.166 --> 49:38.708
I'm in finance.
Mm.

49:40.000 --> 49:41.750
Sounds boring.

49:41.750 --> 49:44.375
No!
No, not today.

49:44.375 --> 49:46.208
Today,
I kicked ass at work,

49:46.208 --> 49:48.875
yeah, big project I've spent
the last few weeks on.

49:48.875 --> 49:51.500
Whose ass
did you kick?

49:51.500 --> 49:52.708
Rhoades.

49:52.708 --> 49:53.959
Big time.

49:53.959 --> 49:55.291
Pounded a company
he's in.

49:55.291 --> 49:58.834
Your friends at the bar helped.
Everyone stepped up.

49:58.834 --> 50:01.708
Good.

50:05.375 --> 50:08.458
Those don't look
like Bruno's.

50:08.458 --> 50:09.500
Mm.
Fuck Bruno.

50:11.583 --> 50:13.959
Ryan did those up
in the wood-burning oven.

50:17.166 --> 50:19.750
Remember our real
first date?

50:27.750 --> 50:29.000
Caviar.

50:29.000 --> 50:30.834
I was trying
to dazzle you.

50:32.417 --> 50:34.750
Well, you did.

50:39.417 --> 50:42.291
I didn't even like
that stuff back then.

50:42.291 --> 50:45.041
Ah, you got used to it.

50:57.041 --> 50:58.875
Mmm.

50:58.875 --> 51:02.625
Still is better
than anchovies.

51:02.625 --> 51:04.500
That's for fucking sure.

51:04.500 --> 51:07.708
Mmm.

51:14.291 --> 51:19.333
